notesStmt.note: Title of first work from introduction (f. 1v); title of second work from colophon (f. 27r); title of third work from title on flyleaf (flyleaf 6 recto); title of fourth work from colophon (f. 100r).

msContents.summary: Set of 4 works copied together two in Arabic, two in Persian. The handwriting changes on f. 29v, near the beginning of the third work.

author.persName: Ījī, ʻAḍud al-Dīn ʻAbd al-Raḥmān ibn Aḥmad, -1355?
ايجي، عضد الدين عبد الرحمن بن احمد،

supportDesc.extent: 100 leaves : 185 x 85 (115 x 45) mm, bound to 185 x 90 mm

layoutDesc.layout: 12-18 lines per page. Catchwords on versos, lower left.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Written in naskh and nastaʻlīq in black ink; pointed, unvocalized.

decoDesc.decoNote: Rubrications in red; diagrams and tables in red and black.

binding.p: Bound in reddish leather over pasteboard; leather is cracked with parts of spine and corner missing. Blind stamped central cartouche with blind tooled frame. Marbled paper doublure.

origin.p: First work dated 9 Muḥarram 982 AH (f. 26r); second work undated; third work dated 982 AH; fourth work dated 985 AH (f. 100r).

history.provenance: Formerly owned by George A. Plimpton (bookplates inside front and back covers).
